Ford Motor Company To Cut Production At Two German Plants-Reuters
Wednesday, 7 Mar 2012 02:46pm EST
Reuters reported that Ford, is cutting production at its two German manufacturing plants in Cologne and Saarlouis, Ford Germany head Bernhard Mattes told Reuters. "Politicians must be ready to allow a restructuring of the market," Mattes said in an interview, referring to the need to trim excess production capacity. Mattes did not give details on the extent of the production cutbacks envisaged.Â 
